---
title: Herbed Beef Tenderloin & Gravy with Rosemary Brown Butter Veggies & Roasted Potatoes
description: We believe pork chops are a canvas. Tonight’s palette for your palate: A savory coating that includes garlic and paprika, and a creamy shallot- and thyme-flecked gravy that’s a work of art in itself—homey and elevated at the same time. Complement those chops with rosemary-brown butter potatoes, parsnips, and carrots, and you’ll have a dinner to Remem-brandt.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/642307efb2f507d6af0e56ee-46ce29cb.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/65d64958dc1b8ee2a5df7e3f.pdf
time required: 45 minutes
cuisine: North America
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
nutrition:
  calories: 820 kcal
  fat: 45 g
  saturated fat: 19 g
  carbohydrates: 67 g
  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 36 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 760 mg
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/herbed-beef-tenderloin-and-gravy-65d64958dc1b8ee2a5df7e3f
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @parsnips{6%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{6%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Slice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ¼-inch-thick rounds. Halve, peel, and mince half the @shallot{1}(minced) (all for 4). Strip @rosemary{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves until you have ½ tsp (1 tsp for 4).

> TIP: If you have any extra rosemary sprigs, save them for an easy garnish!

Toss parsnips and carrots on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Toss potatoes on empty side with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. (For 4 servings, divide between 2 sheets; roast parsnips and carrots on top rack and potatoes on middle rack.)

Pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @fry seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @dried thyme{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

> Swap in chicken or beef for pork. Cook chicken until browned and cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or cook beef to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per side.

In same pan, melt @butter{1%tablespoon} over medium heat. Add minced shallot and cook, stirring, until softened and fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @flour{1%tablespoon}, and a pinch of @dried thyme{}; cook, stirring, until lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Whisk in @water{1%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, and @salt{¼%tsp}. (For 4, use 2 cups of water and ½ tsp salt.) Bring to a simmer, whisking constantly, until thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Remove from heat; stir in @cream cheese{2%tablespoon} until thoroughly combined. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

> Use pan used for chicken or beef here.

Melt @butter{2%tablespoon} in a medium pan over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring frequently, until butter is foamy and flecked with amber brown bits, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in rosemary. Carefully transfer rosemary brown butter to a #medium bowl{}.

Slice pork crosswise.

Add carrots and parsnips to bowl with rosemary brown butter; toss to coat.

Divide pork, carrots and parsnips, and potatoes between plates. Spoon gravy over pork and serve.

> Slice chicken or beef against the grain.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.